As with every North American Arms Mini-Revolver, the hammer need not rest on an empty chamber.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Refurbished Authentic Scout 13' Fiberglass Duck/Fishing Skiff w/25hp Mercury, Gator Trailer, & Gear
postcontent:
A true piece of Lowcountry History, this 72 original Scout was designed and handcrafted at what was then The Outboard Shop in Charleston, SC.  Some background history:  The owner and founder of internationally recognized Scout Boats in Summerville, SC, Mr. Steve Potts, had his beginnings at The Outboard Shop helping to build these awesome skiffs, and was quite fond of the boat and the name. So much so, that later in the 80's when he founded the boat manufacturing company, he named it Scout Boats. 

 Always garage stored, she is now a refurbished 13' Fiberglass Duck/Fishing Skiff that is powered by a Mercury (Model 25E) 25hp Motor, and trailered on a Gator Galvanized Trailer. The Scout has superb fiberglass integrity, and has recently undergone a professional refinish in a palmetto camo pattern.  She has stick steering and throttle controls from the front seat position, which allows the boat to traverse over debris easier.  The vessel can also draft in 4-6 inches of water.  To the right and under the front seat is a large storage compartment, and on the left, a live-well with a system that allows fresh oxygenated water to constantly circulate in the well.  She has a newly installed electric starter and depth finder, two 6 gallon tanks, automatic/selective bilge pump, and a fully charged battery with cover. There are also numerous pieces of equipment included to insure compliance with federal and state laws.  Some of the items are: 3 life jackets, flares, air horn, fire extinguisher, etc.  There are also extra parts and accessories such as spark plugs, fuel/oil mixing bottle, anchor, light pole, lights, motor muffs, wheel chalks, etc.  

The 25hp Mercury Motor is also in superb condition, and has also been refinished in the same camo pattern.  It cranks on command, maintains great compression, has a strong impeller with 20hrs on it, and a new stainless steel prop. She'll run around 30mph fully loaded. 

The galvanized Gator trailer is in excellent condition, and has the following NEW parts:  2 tires, lights all the way around, straight tongue coupler, trailer wire connector, and safety chains with grab hooks.  It comes equipped with a loading crank/winch & tongue jack.  To top this package off, a custom folding grass duck blind is being included in the sale, as well as several sheets of camo burlap. 

Bottom line, you are getting an exceptional, and in immaculate condition, turn-key package that is a special part of Charleston & Boating History. She will be a smart investment, and offer many years of hunting/fishing/recreational pleasure. 

$2500 ALL IN CASH PRICE.  TRADE VALUE IS $3000.  OPEN TO NICE GOLF CART, ATV, OR GUNS PLUS CASH. 

*Clear titles on both the boat & motor.  Registration good until 2017.

title: For Sale:  FNH (5.7X28) SS192 RARE MILITARY GRADE AMMO !!!
postcontent: I am selling some of my FNH (5.7 X 28) SS192 ammo. Here is your chance !! According to Wikipedia; In 2004, the SS192 hollow-point cartridge was introduced. After being met with controversy, the SS192 variety was discontinued in the same year. The SS192 was classified by the ATF as not armor-piercing, and in testing by FNH USA it did not penetrate a Level IIIA vest when fired from the Five-seven pistol. The article does not mention anything about the penetrating effectiveness when fired from the FNH PS90. According to Wikipedia; In early 2005, the pistol was the subject of intense controversy in the United States after the Brady Campaign stated that commercially available SS192 ammunition penetrated a Level IIA Kevlar vest in testing. In additional tests conducted by FN Herstal USA, FN_Herstal USA would only say that SS192 ammunition was unable to penetrate Level IIIA vests, as opposed to the Level IIA vest that was reportedly penetrated in tests by the Brady Campaign. FN_Herstal USA discontinued import of the SS192 at this time. Does the SS192 ammo have armor piercing capabilities in the 5.7 pistol ? Does the SS192 ammo have piercing capabilities in the PS90 ? SS192 specifications: - 28 grain copper jacket hollow points. - muzzle velocity = 2350 (ft/s). - SS197 muzzle velocity = 1,950 (ft/s). - muzzle energy = 467 J (344 ft-lb). - SS197 muzzle energy = 461 J (340 ft-lb). - effective range = 660 ft. This ammo is very rare and there are very limited quantities available anywhere. I don't remember the last time I saw any available on this website.  I am selling each box of 50 for $55.00.  I have very limited quantities available.  Local face to face is prefered (20 minute drive time maximum on my part) - but I will ship after payment is received and cleared.
